                <note rend="inline" type="source">500.A15A4/1851: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        American Delegate</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Wilson</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-05-09T17:00:00-04:00"
                            >May 9, 1933—5 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>330. Your 630, May 6, 11 a.m. Your suggested reply to Saavedra approved,
                    particularly your emphasis on the importance of introducing the figures for
                    Latin American countries prior to signature of convention.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
